All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of what was fixed:

**Bug:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```typescript
// Before (buggy) — stops one short, skipping the last element
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed) — processes all elements including the last
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The `- 1` in the loop condition caused the loop to exit before reaching the final index, so the last item was always silently dropped. Removing it lets the loop run through the full array.

